ttle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda was born about 1152, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir William de Baguley in 1170, in Huyton, Lancashire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"ABT. 1152–":"umbes 1152–Surnud","1148–1231":"1148–1231","1172–Male":"1172–Surnud","1152–Female":"1152–Surnud","ABT. 1152":"umbes 1152","1148":"1148","1231":"1231","1152":"1152","1172":"1172","1170":"1170","Huyton, Lancashire, England":"Huyton, Lancashire, England","of Boothes, Chester, Eng.":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bagulet Bucklow, Cheshire, England":"Bucklow Hill, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT. 1152–":"noin 1152–Kuollut","1148–1231":"1148–1231","1172–Male":"1172–Kuollut","1152–Female":"1152–Kuollut","ABT. 1152":"noin 1152","1148":"1148","1231":"1231","1152":"1152","1172":"1172","1170":"1170","Huyton, Lancashire, England":"Huyton, Lancashire, England","of Boothes, Chester, Eng.":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bagulet Bucklow, Cheshire, England":"Bucklow Hill, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT. 1152–":"environ 1152–Décédée","1148–1231":"1148–1231","1172–Male":"1172–Décédé","1152–Female":"1152–Décédée","ABT. 1152":"environ 1152","1148":"1148","1231":"1231","1152":"1152","1172":"1172","1170":"1170","Huyton, Lancashire, England":"Huyton, Lancashire, Angleterre","of Boothes, Chester, Eng.":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bagulet Bucklow, Cheshire, England":"Buck